                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.34112 RP/7–1244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reed</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-12T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 12, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received, 9:11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>387. The Undersecretary of Foreign Relations<note n="76" xml:id="d1403fn76">Mario
                        Ferrario.</note> told me this morning that the President is interested in
                    removing all the quebracho properties in Paraguay from foreign control and that
                    instructions are being sent to Ambassador Velasquez to approach the Department
                    with a view to an Export Bank loan for purchasing them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reed</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
